<DocsHero
  @prefix=''
  @heading='ember-jsQR'
  @byline='an integration with a very fast QR Code scanner'
/>

<div class="docs-container docs-md docs-my-16">
  <section class="docs-section docs-max-w-md docs-mx-auto docs-pb-8">
    <h2 class='docs-text-large-5 docs-font-bold docs-mb-4'>Introduction</h2>

    <p>
      <em>ember-jsqr</em> is a small addon that implements a specific use case for
      integrating with
      <a
        class='docs-text-brand-var'
        href='https://github.com/cozmo/jsQR'
        target='_blank'
        rel='noopener noreferrer'
      >
        jsqr
      </a>
      without adding to your bundle size.
      <br><br>
      It assumes:
      <ul class='docs-list-disc docs-list-inside docs-p-4'>
        <li>you want visual indication of when a QR Code is detected</li>
        <li>you want to be in control of selecting the camera</li>
        <li>you want to be in control of when to start / stop scanning</li>
        <li>you target environments taht support dynamic imports</li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <div class="docs-my-5 docs-text-right">
      {{#docs-link "docs"}}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="docs-bg-grey-darkest docs-text-white docs-py-2 docs-px-4 docs-no-underline docs-rounded hover:docs-bg-black"
        >
          Get started &rarr;
        </button>
      {{/docs-link}}
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
